Bernanke Says Fed Can Resort to More Stimulus Action If Conditions Warrant

-- B y   S c o t t   L a n m a n
-- 
2011-06-22T19:01:58Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-22/bernanke-says-fed-can-resort-to-more-stimulus-action-if-conditions-warrant.html
Federal Reserve Chairman  Ben S.
Bernanke  said the central bank can take additional actions to
stimulate the economy “if conditions warranted.”  Potential tools, which have risks or costs, include
additional securities purchases or a reduction in the interest
rate on excess bank reserves, Bernanke said today at a press
conference in  Washington .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Scott Lanman in Washington at 
 slanman@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
